{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cf4187df-9231-446a-884a-5b88b19b5457","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **4.6.0+** (you're already there ✅)\n\n2. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` from your project.\n\n3. **Add** the `NUnit.Testing.Extensions.Microsoft.Testing.Platform` package:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Testing.Extensions.Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n   ```\n\n4. **Enable the new platform** in your project file:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Or run the test executable directly — Microsoft.Testing.Platform generates a standalone test host.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n- The test project compiles to an executable, not a library.\n- CLI options change (e.g., `--filter` becomes `--treenode-filter` when running directly).\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may not apply.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"685010a9-c020-4c40-bd35-2e0da44a51f2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"1BD8:111A97:200E873:236C78C:6A03CDB9"},"id":"4a028656-ea29-4853-b383-ad02a0bb4763","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:02:58.950Z","parentId":"4a6d4d6d-7592-4d4b-8ad0-f39ada1c326f"}
